TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bretscher, Lorenzo
AU  - Hsu, Alex
AU  - Simasek, Peter
AU  - Tamoni, Andrea
T1  - COVID-19 and the Cross-Section of Equity Returns: Impact and Transmission
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raaa017
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
SP  - 705
EP  - 741
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Using the first reported case of COVID-19 in a given U.S. county as the event day, we find that firms headquartered in an affected county experience, on average, a 27-bps lower return in the 10-day post-event window. This negative effect nearly doubles in magnitude for firms in counties with a higher infection rate (−50 bps). We test a number of transmission channels. Firms belonging to labor-intensive industries and those located in counties with a large mobility decline have worse stock performance. Firms sensitive to COVID-19-induced uncertainty also exhibit more negative returns. Finally, more negative stock returns are associated with downward revisions in earnings forecasts.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raaa017
ER  - 



